solution:
Of the 5 boxes with pencils, 2 have pens also, so $5-2=3$ have pencils only.  Similarly, $4-2 =2$ of the boxes have pens only:


[asy]
unitsize(0.05cm);
label("Pencils", (2,74));
label("Pens", (80,74));
draw(Circle((30,45), 22));
draw(Circle((58, 45), 22));
label("$2$", (44, 45));
label(scale(0.8)*"$3$",(28,58));
label(scale(0.8)*"$2$",(63,58));
[/asy]

That gives us $3+2+2=7$ boxes with pens, pencils, or both.  This leaves $10-7 = \boxed{3}$ with neither.

